Classifications.Name: Pump
Classifications.Definition: Pump is the representation of a Pump and organizes its properties in classifications.

Classifications.Name: Documentation
Classifications.Definition: Documentation provides various properties for links to documents that are used for maintenance operations.

Classifications.Name: GeneralMaintenance
Classifications.Definition: GeneralMaintenance provides properties that are used for general maintenance applications.

Classifications.Name: ConditionBasedMaintenance
Classifications.Definition: ConditionBasedMaintenance provides properties that are used for condition based maintenance.

Classifications.Name: PreventiveMaintenance
Classifications.Definition: PreventiveMaintenance provides properties that are used for preventive maintenance.

Classifications.Name: BreakdownMaintenance
Classifications.Definition: BreakdownMaintenance provides properties that are used for breakdown maintenance.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionMechanics
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionMechanics provides properties used for monitoring the Pump mechanics.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionHardware
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionHardware provides properties used for monitoring the Pump hardware.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionSoftware
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionSoftware provides properties used for monitoring the Pump software.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionProcessFluid
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionProcessFluid provides properties used for monitoring the Pump process fluid.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionPumpOperation
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionPumpOperation provides properties used for monitoring the Pump operation.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionAuxiliary
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionAuxiliaryDevice provides properties used for monitoring the Pump auxiliary devices.

Classifications.Name: SupervisionElectronics
Classifications.Definition: SupervisionElectronics provides properties used for monitoring the Pump electronics.

Classifications.Name: Design
Classifications.Definition: Design provides static properties for design properties, describing the limitations and working conditions of a Pump.

Classifications.Name: SystemRequirements
Classifications.Definition: SystemRequirements provides static properties for parameters of the process in which the Pump is to be used.

Classifications.Name: Implementation
Classifications.Definition: Implementation provides static properties for preconfiguring a Pump for the process in which the Pump is to be used.

Classifications.Name: Control
Classifications.Definition: Control provides properties for precise control of a Pump according to DIN IEC 60050-351.

Classifications.Name: Measurements
Classifications.Definition: Measurements provides properties used for measurements performed at a Pump.

Classifications.Name: MultiPump
Classifications.Definition: MultiPump provides properties for pump operation in a system with several pumps.

Classifications.Name: Actuation
Classifications.Definition: Actuation provides general propertues for asset actuation.

Classifications.Name: PumpActuation
Classifications.Definition: PumpActuation extends its supertype (Actuation) by Pump specific proerties and Classifications for discrete outputs according to VDMA 24223.

Classifications.Name: CleanValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the clean valve.

Classifications.Name: FlushValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the flush valve.

Classifications.Name: GasDilValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the gas dilution valve.

Classifications.Name: InletValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the inlet valve.

Classifications.Name: OutletValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the outlet valve.

Classifications.Name: PumpStandByRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for pump standby.

Classifications.Name: PurgeValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This element offers a request for the opening of the purge valve.

Classifications.Name: VentValveRequest
Classifications.Definition: This property indicates the inversion of the standard rotating direction.

Classifications.Name: PumpKick
Classifications.Definition: This element describes a periodical operation of a pump, avoiding blockage at non operation time.

Classifications.Name: Signals
Classifications.Definition: Signals provides Classifications to provide feedback properties on the current Pump state.

Classifications.Name: Acceleration
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump rotation accelerates.

Classifications.Name: CleanValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the cleaning valve.

Classifications.Name: Deceleration
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump rotation decelerates.

Classifications.Name: FlushValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the flush valve.

Classifications.Name: GasDilValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the gas dilution valve.

Classifications.Name: InletValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the inlet valve.

Classifications.Name: NoRotation
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump stands still.

Classifications.Name: OutletValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the outlet valve.

Classifications.Name: ProcessIsActive
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the process is active.

Classifications.Name: PumpActivation
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the activation state of the pump. The activation state takes into account that control mechanisms are active. Never the less the pump is not necessarily running

Classifications.Name: PumpDirection
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback of the pumps direction of rotation.

Classifications.Name: PumpOperation
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the operation state of the pump. In the operation state the pump rotor is rotating.

Classifications.Name: PumpPowerMax
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback of pump operating at maximum power.

Classifications.Name: PumpSpeedMax
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback of pump operating at maximum speed.

Classifications.Name: PumpSpeedMin
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump operates at minimum speed.

Classifications.Name: PurgeValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the purge valve.

Classifications.Name: RatedSpeed
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump rotation is at rated speed.

Classifications.Name: StandBy
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the process standby of the pump. In the stand by state the pump is ready for operation.

Classifications.Name: StandBySpeed
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump rotation is at standby speed.

Classifications.Name: TargetSpeed
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback that the pump is at target speed.

Classifications.Name: VentValveOpen
Classifications.Definition: This element serves a feedback about the open state of the vent valve.

Classifications.Name: Identication
Classifications.Definition: Identification provides properties for a globally unique identification, vendor defined information, and user-specific information of a pump.

Classifications.Name: Port
Classifications.Definition: Port provides Classifications for identification and specification of a Pump Port.

Classifications.Name: DrivePort
Classifications.Definition: (Port) by Classifications for pump drive specific properties.

Classifications.Name: DriveDesign
Classifications.Definition: Manufacturer's properties that describe the rudimentary data of the drive.

Classifications.Name: DriveMeasurements
Classifications.Definition: All operation measurements that describe the drive.

Classifications.Name: InletConnectionPort
Classifications.Definition: InletConnectionPort extends its supertype (Port) by Classifications for pump inlet specific properties.

Classifications.Name: InletConnectionDesign
Classifications.Definition: Manufacturer's properties that describe the rudimentary data of the inlet connection.

Classifications.Name: InletConnectionImplementation
Classifications.Definition: Properties that describe the specific installation and operational situation of the inlet connection.

Classifications.Name: InletConnectionMeasurements
Classifications.Definition: All measurements of the operation which describe the inlet connection.

Classifications.Name: InletConnectionSystemRequirements
Classifications.Definition: Buyer's properties that describe the installation situation of the inlet port.

Classifications.Name: OutletConnectionPort
Classifications.Definition: OutletConnectionPort extends its supertype (Port) by Classifications for pump outlet specific properties.

Classifications.Name: OutletConnectionDesign
Classifications.Definition: Manufacturer's properties that describe the rudimentary data of the outlet connection.

Classifications.Name: OutletConnectionImplementation
Classifications.Definition: Properties that describe the specific installation and operational situation of the outlet connection.

Classifications.Name: OutletConnectionMeasurements
Classifications.Definition: All measurements of the operation which describe the outlet connection.

Classifications.Name: OutletConnectionSystemRequirements
Classifications.Definition: Buyer's properties that describe the installation situation of the outlet port.

Properties.Name: ArrangementsLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to drawing showing replacement components layout for an item.

Properties.Name: CertificatesLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to specific safety and statutory regulations certificates for items (lifting equipment, steam boilers, pressure vessels,...).

Properties.Name: CircuitDiagramLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to overall feeder and control circuits diagram.

Properties.Name: ComponentsListLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to comprehensive list of items which constitute part of another one.

Properties.Name: DetailLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to drawing with part list to ensure dismantling, repair and assembly of items.

Properties.Name: DuringMaintenanceServicesRenderedLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to final and/or interim report on services provided

Properties.Name: ImplementationDescriptionLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to explanation of the work carried out

Properties.Name: LayoutLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to drawing showing all areas of a particular plant.

Properties.Name: LocationLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to drawing showing the position of all field items within the considered area.

Properties.Name: LogicDiagramLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to system control diagram to clarify the overall system logic.

Properties.Name: LubricationMapLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to drawing showing position of each item lubrication point, with lubrication data and specifications.

Properties.Name: MaintenanceManualLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to technical instructions intended to preserve an item in, or restore it to, a state in which it can perform a required function.

Properties.Name: OperationManualLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to technical instructions to reach a proper item function performance according to its technical specifications and safety conditions.

Properties.Name: PersonnelRecordingLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to list of all activities (work order) performed by a technician. This list includes a predefined time period

Properties.Name: PipeAndInstrumentDiagramLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to overall fluid conduction (air, steam, oil, fuel ...), and control diagram.

Properties.Name: ScopeOfWorkLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to the hours worked in the execution of the work order. The type of hours worked should be indicated: normal, in shifts, at night, overtime, etc.

Properties.Name: SingleLineDiagramLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to overall power distribution diagram (electrical, pneumatic, hydraulic). This kind of diagram includes switchboard circuits.

Properties.Name: SparePartReferenceLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to list of all spare parts used within the scope of the work order

Properties.Name: StaffLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to list of all maintenance workers involved in the execution of the work order

Properties.Name: TechnicalDataLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to manufacturer`s specification of the item.

Properties.Name: TestProgramReportLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to commissioning report which demonstrates that an item is in compliance with specifications.

Properties.Name: UnitMaintenanceReportLink
Properties.Description: Weblink to list of work orders for a particular unit. The list is created for a specified period of time

Properties.Name: ActiveMaintenanceTime
Properties.Description: Part of the maintenance time when active maintenance is carried out on an item

Properties.Name: DownTime
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in a down state

Properties.Name: ExternalDisabledTime
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in an external disabled state

Properties.Name: FailureRate
Properties.Description: Number of failures within a population divided by the number of life units used by that population

Properties.Name: IdleTime
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in an idle state

Properties.Name: MaintenanceLevel
Properties.Description: Maintenance task categorization by complexity

AllowedValues.Description: Level 1 is characterized by simple actions carried out with minimal training
Level 2 is characterized by basic actions which have to be carried out by qualified personnel using detailed procedures
Level 3 is characterized by complex actions carried out by qualified technical personnel using detailed procedures
Level 4 is characterized by actions which imply the know-how of a technique or a technology and carried out by specialized technical personnel
Level 5 is characterized by actions which imply a knowledge held by the manufacturer or a specialized company with industrial logistic support equipment

Properties.Name: MaintenanceTime
Properties.Description: Time interval when maintenance is carried out on an item including technical, logistic and internal administrative delays

Properties.Name: MeanOperatingTimeBetweenFailures
Properties.Description: Average of the operating times between failures

Properties.Name: MeanRepairTime
Properties.Description: Average of the repair times

Properties.Name: MeanTimeToRestauration
Properties.Description: Average of the time to restauration

Properties.Name: Obsolescence
Properties.Description: Inability of an item to be maintained due to the unavailability on the market of the necessary resources at acceptable technical and/or economic conditions. A "True" status means that the pump is obsolete and a "False" status means that the pump is not obsolete.

Properties.Name: OperatingTime
Properties.Description: Operating time between consecutive failures

Properties.Name: OperatingTimeBetweenFailures
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in operating state

Properties.Name: OperatingTimeToFailure
Properties.Description: Operating time accumulated from the first use, or from restoration, until failure

Properties.Name: RepairTime
Properties.Description: Part of corrective maintenance time when repair is carried out on an item.

Properties.Name: StandbyTime
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in a standby state

Properties.Name: StateOfTheItem
Properties.Description: Current state of the item

AllowedValues.Description: Item is in up state and non-operating outside required time
Item is in up state and non-operating during required time
Item is in up state and operating as required
Item is in up state, but lacks required external resources or is disabled due to planned actions other than maintenance
Item is unable to perform a required function due to preventive maintenance or a fault

Properties.Name: TimeBetweenFailures
Properties.Description: Duration between consecutive failures

Properties.Name: TimeToRestoration
Properties.Description: Time interval, from the instant of failure, until restoration

Properties.Name: UpTime
Properties.Description: Measured time interval throughout which an item is in an up state

Properties.Name: Availability
Properties.Description: Probability that a machine will, when used under specified conditions, operate satisfactorily and effectively

Properties.Name: Durability
Properties.Description: Actual reliability of an item considering operating modes, operating conditions and possible preventive maintenance actions carried out

Properties.Name: ExpectedReliability
Properties.Description: Reliability of an item determined by design and manufacture under expected conditions of operation and maintenance

Properties.Name: InstantaneousAvailability
Properties.Description: Probability that an item is in a state to perform as required at a given instant, under given conditions, assuming that the necessary external resources are provided

Properties.Name: IntrinsicMaintainability
Properties.Description: Maintainability of an item determined by the design under expected conditions of maintenance and logistic support

Properties.Name: IntrinsicReliability
Properties.Description: Reliability of an item determined by design and manufacture un­der expected conditions of operation assuming that no preven­tive maintenance task is carried out, excepting routine mainte­nance

Properties.Name: Maintainability
Properties.Description: Ability of a machine or part of a system to be retained in, or re­stored to, a state in which it can perform the required function(s)

Properties.Name: OperationalReliability
Properties.Description: Actual reliability of an item considering operating modes, operating conditions and possible preventive maintenance actions carried out

Properties.Name: ProductionBasedAvailability
Properties.Description: Ratio of actual production to required production, or any other reference level, over a specified period of time

Properties.Name: Reliability
Properties.Description: Probability that a machine will perform its required functions without failure for a specified time period when used under specified conditions

Properties.Name: TimeBasedAvailability
Properties.Description: During a given period of time, percentage of the time during which an item was able to perform when required

Properties.Name: ActivePreventiveMaintenanceTime
Properties.Description: This attribute indicates the date of installation or commissioning of the device.

Properties.Name: InstallationDate
Properties.Description: This attribute identifies the date when the device was last inspected.

Properties.Name: NextInspectionDate

Properties.Name: PreventiveMaintenanceTime

Properties.Name: CorrectiveMaintenanceTime

Properties.Name: Criticality
